It is, but I figured that if somebody changes the size of `cfg.mServiceData` in the future to be greater than 255, and changed the length parameter to a wider type (e.g. uint16_t), then unknowingly to the author it'd be possible to specify a length that overflows because of the narrowing cast on line 872: `static_cast<uint8_t>(dataLen)`.

Perhaps it'd be better to split this out in to static assert, something like:
```
VerifyOrExit((dataLen <= sizeof(cfg.mServiceData), error = OT_ERROR_INVALID_ARGS);
OT_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(cfg.mServiceData) <= UINT8_MAX, "Invalid cast to uint8");
```

