I'm afraid that `RpcReferenceCache` is pointing to the same instance as `this`.  The reason of my question was that we should limit the scope of synchronization only to `RpcReferenceCache`. Another thread could acquire lock  outside of `RpcReferenceCache` and this might lead to problems. Apologize, I should have been more explicit about this problem.

This will cause a deadlock for instance: 
```
object SomeObject {
  assert(this == SomeObject)
  def someMethod() = synchronized {
    println(this)
    println("Hello World!")
  }
}

object Application extends App {
  SomeObject.synchronized{
    val thread = new Thread(
      new Runnable {
        def run(): Unit = {
          SomeObject.someMethod()
        }
      })
    thread.start()
    thread.join()
  }
}
```

I good practice is to create a private instance dedicated just for locking. WDYT?

